{"lemma":"عِراقٌ","slug":"عِراقٌ","root":"ع.ر.ق","root_slug":"ع-ر-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ر-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":12},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28785","n28786"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%90%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"only used in العِرَاق (al-ʕirāq, “Iraq”)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"only used in عِرَاق الْعَجَم (ʕirāq al-ʕajam)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"only used in عِرَاق الْعَرَب (ʕirāq al-ʕarab)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a double suture that is at the lower end of a waterskin (مَزَادَة (mazāda) or قِرْبَة (qirba)) or eating mat (سُفْرَة (sufra))","tags":["Classical"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shore, coast, any region or area (of a whole country or a mere rivulet in a garden) adjacent to water as opposed to another one","tags":["Classical"],"examples":[{"text":"ومثل الألبان والرواصيل والبليلج فإنها غذاء لأهل الجبال وسم لأهل العراق","english":"And likewise, milk and confitures and myrobalans are food for mountain dwellers and poison for shore people."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the circuit or surrounding edge of the ear","tags":["Classical"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the fore part and hinder part of the saddle of a horse","tags":["Classical"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the court or yard extending from the sides of the house","tags":["Classical"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pace, rate of going","tags":["Classical"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"clear water","tags":["Classical"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"copious rain","tags":["Classical"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a picked bone, the fleshmeat of bone","tags":["Classical"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕi.raːq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28785","headword_ar":"عُرَاقٌ","root":"Erq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaroqN","text_ar":"عَرْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places. ―         -b2-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuraAqapN","text_ar":"عُرَاقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuTofapN","text_ar":"نُطْفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina AlmaA='i","text_ar":"مِنَ المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Clear water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"whether"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"little;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a little water remaining in a bucket"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) or, accord. to the L, the former word is pl. [or rather a coll. gen. n.] of the latter in this sense: (TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaroqaApN","text_ar":"عَرْقَاةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same. (K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A copious rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuraAqapN","text_ar":"عُرَاقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[only]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuraAqu Algayovi","text_ar":"عُرَاقُ الغَيْثِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The herbage that has come forth after the rain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, A, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["O","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n28786","headword_ar":"عِرَاقٌ","root":"Erq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"double suture that is in the lower part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the [leathern water-bag called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mazaAdap","text_ar":"مَزَادَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAwiyap","text_ar":"رَاوِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lth, O, K;) and this is of the firmest kinds of suture therein: (Lth, O:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suture that is in the middle"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qirobap","text_ar":"قِرْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or water-skin]: (TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strip"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of skin that is put upon the place where the two extremities,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"edges, of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"main"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skin meet when it is sewed in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon, the lower part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mzAdp","text_ar":"مزادة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appertenance"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrbp","text_ar":"قربة"},{"kind":"text","text":", and of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mzAdp","text_ar":"مزادة"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a strip of skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"doubled and then sewed"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thereon thus"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"doubled:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or, accord. to AZ, the ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skin that is doubled, and then sewed upon the lower part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the [water-skin or milk-skin called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siqaA='","text_ar":"سِقَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and, (K,) accord. to As, (S, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TibaAbapN","text_ar":"طِبَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, K;) i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of skin with which the punctures of the seams are covered:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O: see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraqN","text_ar":"عَرَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", latter half: [and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TibaAbapN","text_ar":"طِبَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuruqN","text_ar":"عُرُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, AZ, S, O, K, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuroqN","text_ar":"عُرْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoriqapN","text_ar":"اَعْرِقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lth, O, TA;) the last a pl. of pauc. (Lth, O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiraAqu Als~uforapi","text_ar":"عِرَاقُ السُّفْرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The suture surrounding the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"round piece of skin called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suforap","text_ar":"سُفْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (K.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nearness, together, of the stitch-holes"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a skin or hide: [so I render"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqaArubu Alxrzi","text_ar":"تَقَارُبُ الخرزِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; reading"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxurazi","text_ar":"الخُرَزِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and it seems to mean also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uniformity thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for it is added,] hence the prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liA^amorihi EiraAqN","text_ar":"لِاَمْرِهِ عِرَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His affair is uniform, right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rightly disposed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shore,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, O, K,) of water, (K,) or of a sea, or great river,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"along the whole length"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof. (Lth, O, K. * [It is said in the K that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuruqN","text_ar":"عُرُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiraAqN","text_ar":"عِرَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this sense: but afterwards, that the pl. of the latter in all its senses is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoriqapN","text_ar":"اَعْرِقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also; to which the TA adds"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuroqN","text_ar":"عُرْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And accord. to AZ,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any pasturage adjacent to a great river"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sea."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiraAqu Aln~ahori","text_ar":"عِرَاقُ النَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~akiybi","text_ar":"الرَّكِيبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The border of the rivulet"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for irrigation"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by which the water enters a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAy^iT","text_ar":"حَايِط"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garden,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garden of palm-trees surrounded by a wall"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from its nearest to its furthest extremity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b4-  Also The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quTor","text_ar":"قُطْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side"},{"kind":"text","text":"(but see this word)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a mountain, by itself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or so, perhaps,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiraAqu jabalK","text_ar":"عِرَاقُ جَبَلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiroqN","text_ar":"عِرْقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiroqu jabalK","text_ar":"عِرْقُ جَبَلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Ibn-'Abbád, O, K.) ―         -b5-  And, as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiroqN","text_ar":"عِرْقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Remains of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trees, called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoD","text_ar":"حَمْض"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiraAqu Ald~aAri","text_ar":"عِرَاقُ الدَّارِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The court,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yard, in front,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extending from the sides, of the house."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IB, K.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiraAqu AlA^u*uni","text_ar":"عِرَاقُ الاُذُنِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The circuit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surrounding edge, of the ear."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiraAqu AlZ~ufuri","text_ar":"عِرَاقُ الظُّفُرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The flesh surrounding the nail."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiraAqu AlHa$aA","text_ar":"عِرَاقُ الحَشَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The intestines that are above the navel, lying breadthwise,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"across, in the belly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b10-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiraAqN","text_ar":"عِرَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inside of feathers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, K.) ―         -b11-  The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiraAqaAni","text_ar":"عِرَاقَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the horse's saddle are The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two edges of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daf~ataAni","text_ar":"دَفَّتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the fore part of the saddle and its hinder part."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qarabuwsN","text_ar":"قَرَبُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.)       -A2-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A pace,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rate of going."},{"kind":"text","text":"] One says in relation to a horse, on the occasion of drawing forth the sweat, and of careful tending, and fattening,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiHomilohu EalaY AlEiraAqi","text_ar":"اِحْمِلْهُ عَلَى العِرَاقِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aEolaY waAlEiraAqi AlA^asofali","text_ar":"الاَعْلَى وَالعِرَاقِ الاَسْفَلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Urge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"make, thou him to go"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the vehement pace and the inferior pace."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, O, TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEiraAqu","text_ar":"العِرَاقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extending from 'Abbádán to El-Mow- sil in length and from El-Kádiseeyeh to Hulwán in breadth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) masc. and fem.: (S, O, Msb, K:) said to be so named because upon the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiraAq","text_ar":"عِرَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. “ side, ” or “ shore, ” of the Tigris and Euphrates: (O, * K: [in which, and in other works, several other supposed derivations are mentioned, but such as I think too fanciful to deserve notice:]) accord. to some, it is arabicized, (S, O, Msb, K,) from a Pers. appellation, (S, O,) i. e. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyraAn $ahor","text_ar":"اـِيرَان شَهْر"},{"kind":"text","text":", (As, O, * K, TA,) of which the meaning is [said to be] “ having many palmtrees and [other] trees; ” (K;) but [SM justly says,] in my opinion the meaning requires consideration. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEiraAqaAni","text_ar":"العِرَاقَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appellation of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"El-Basrah and El-Koofeh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["Lth","O","TA","K","Msb","S","AZ"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}